<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1523,1764]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1523,1548]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[542,629,1524,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis box="[542,629,1524,1548]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the wing pattern and the male genitalia features (see diagnosis under that species). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[308,594,1560,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rubromarginata" subSpecies="indica">
<emphasis box="[308,594,1560,1584]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. rubromarginata indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from the nominate subspecies by larger size, and some differences in the wing pattern and the male genitalia. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[793,1076,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rubromarginata" subSpecies="indica">
<emphasis box="[793,1076,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. rubromarginata indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ground colour of the wings and the shadow on the forewing from apex to the middle of the inner margin is paler than in the nominate subspecies. The posterior margins of the uncus lobes are truncate, and their apical angles are less swollen than in the nominate subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
